cp (short for copy) this command is used for copying files or directories, but it also has few more operating options.
- Copy the content of file or directory from a file to another one, creating the second file if it was neccesary.
- Copy the files from one place into one directory, creating the directory one if it was neccesary.
- Copy every files from one directory into another in case it exists, in case it does not, create the directory and copy the files into it.
